HEADWORD: phylogeny
<hw>phy*log"e*ny</hw>
<pr>(f⟦imac⟧*l⟦ocr⟧j"⟦esl⟧*n⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>fy^lon</grk> race, tribe + E. <ets>genesis</ets>, or root of Gr.
<grk>gi`gnesqai</grk> to be born.]</ety> <def>The history of
genealogical development; the sequence of events involved in the
evolutionary development of a species or taxonomic group of organisms;
the historic exolution of the <xex>phylon</xex> or tribe, in distinction
from <contr>ontogeny</contr>, or the development of the individual
organism, and from <xex>biogenesis</xex>, or life development
generally.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> evolution.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

